an’s former futures for the sake of continued, radical world-building.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aFeminism and motion pictures. 0aFeminism in literature. 0aFeminismxHistoryy20th century. 0aFeminist theory. 0aLesbian feminist theory. 0aLesbians in literature. 0aScience fictionxHistory and criticism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478022640?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022640423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022640/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099455-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DSLb2022